## Runbook Linking

### Alert to Runbook

Every alert must link to a runbook.

```yaml
# Prometheus alert with runbook
annotations:
  runbook_url: "https://runbooks.example.com/api-high-error-rate"
  summary: "API error rate above 5%"
```

### Runbook Structure

```markdown
# Runbook: [Alert Name]

## Summary
One-line description of the alert.

## Severity
Critical / High / Medium / Low

## Impact
What users or systems are affected.

## Prerequisites
- Access to [dashboard], [logs]
- Permissions: [list]

## Investigation
1. Check [dashboard link]
2. Look for [pattern] in logs
3. Verify [dependency] is healthy

## Resolution
1. [Step 1 - copy-paste ready]
2. [Step 2]
3. Verify: [success criteria]

## Rollback
If resolution fails: [link to rollback runbook]

## Escalation
Contact: [on-call], [slack channel]
```

### Runbook Quality Checklist

- [ ] Every alert has a runbook
- [ ] Runbook is linked from alert
- [ ] Steps are copy-paste ready
- [ ] Success criteria defined
- [ ] Escalation path documented
- [ ] Runbook tested (drill or incident)

