## Dashboard Standards

### Dashboard Layout

| Section | Content |
|---------|---------|
| Overview | Golden signals, SLO status |
| Traffic | RPS, top endpoints |
| Latency | Histogram, percentiles |
| Errors | Error rate, top error types |
| Saturation | CPU, memory, queue depth |
| Dependencies | Downstream health |

### Dashboard Checklist

- [ ] Golden signals visible at top
- [ ] Time range matches alert window
- [ ] Links to runbooks for each panel
- [ ] No more than 10-15 panels per dashboard
- [ ] Dashboard loads in < 5 seconds

---

## On-Call Readiness

- [ ] Runbooks exist for all paging alerts
- [ ] On-call has access to dashboards and logs
- [ ] Escalation path is documented
- [ ] Post-incident review process exists
- [ ] Alert volume is sustainable (< 2 pages per week per person)
